 0668: # function KahanSum(input)
 0669: #     var sum = 0.0
 0670: #     var c = 0.0                  // A running compensation for lost low-order bits.
 0671: #     for i = 1 to input.length do
 0672: #         var y = input[i] - c     // So far, so good: c is zero.
 0673: #         var t = sum + y          // Alas, sum is big, y small, so low-order digits of y are lost.
 0674: #         c = (t - sum) - y // (t - sum) recovers the high-order part of y; subtracting y recovers -(low part of y)
 0675: #         sum = t           // Algebraically, c should always be zero. Beware overly-aggressive optimizing compilers!
 0676: #         // Next time around, the lost low part will be added to y in a fresh attempt.
 0677: #     return sum
